
JA4+ Zeek Plugin
=================

A compiled Zeek plugin implementing JA4+ network fingerprinting.
Replaces the pure-script implementation with C++ BiF functions for
performance-critical fingerprints.

Fingerprints
------------

C++ accelerated (BiF):
  JA4   - TLS client fingerprint
  JA4S  - TLS server fingerprint
  JA4H  - HTTP client fingerprint
  JA4SSH - SSH traffic fingerprint
  JA4T  - TCP client fingerprint (raw packet parsing)

Pure script (bundled):
  JA4L  - Connection latency
  JA4D  - DHCP fingerprint

Requirements
------------

  Zeek >= 7.0 (tested with 8.0.6)
  C++20 compiler (Clang 19+ or GCC 12+)
  CMake >= 3.15

Build
-----

  cd ja4-plugin
  ./configure
  cd build
  make -j$(nproc)

Or via zkg:

  zkg install .

Usage
-----

  # Plugin auto-loads JA4/JA4S/JA4SSH/JA4T/JA4L/JA4D
  ZEEK_PLUGIN_PATH=/path/to/ja4-plugin/build zeek -C -r trace.pcap

  # JA4H requires explicit loading (HTTP::Info dependency)
  ZEEK_PLUGIN_PATH=/path/to/ja4-plugin/build zeek -C -r trace.pcap /path/to/ja4-plugin/scripts/ja4h

Output: fingerprint fields are added to ssl.log, conn.log, http.log,
and dedicated ja4ssh.log / ja4d.log streams.

Configuration
-------------

Each fingerprint can be toggled in scripts/config.zeek:

  redef FINGERPRINT::JA4_enabled = F;   # disable JA4
  redef FINGERPRINT::JA4H_enabled = F;  # disable JA4H

Tests
-----

  # btest suite (requires btest in PATH)
  cd ja4-plugin/tests && btest

